1 carton(s) Tomato Passata
50 grams Harissa Paste
1 sachet(s) Dried Oregano
10 grams Chicken Stock Paste
250 grams Parma Ham & Parmigiano Reggiano Filled Pasta
1 unit(s) Ciabatta
40 grams Baby Spinach
50 grams Greek Style Salad Cheese
1 tsp Sugar
50 milliliter(s) Water for the Sauce
30 grams Butter

Boil a half-full kettle.
Meanwhile, pop a frying pan on medium heat.
Add the passata, harissa, oregano, chicken stock paste, sugar and water (see pantry for both).
Stir to combine and bring to the boil. Simmer, 4-5 mins.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a saucepan with 1/2 tsp salt on high heat.
Boil the filled pasta, 3 mins.
Drain and drizzle with oil.

Next, halve the ciabatta.
Toast the ciabatta halves in your toaster until golden. Drizzle with oil and season with salt.
Add the butter (see pantry) and spinach to the sauce in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, 1-2 mins.
Stir in the cooked pasta.

Share the pasta between your bowls.
Crumble over the cheese.
Serve the ciabatta alongside.
Enjoy!